==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haulm
<hw>Haulm</hw> <pr>(h⟦add⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>halm</ets>, AS. <ets>healm</ets>; akin to D., G., Dan., & Sw.
<ets>halm</ets>, Icel. <ets>h⟦amac⟧lmr</ets>, L. <ets>calamus</ets>
reed, cane, stalk, Gr. <grk>kalamo`s</grk>. Cf. <er>Excel</er>,
<er>Culminate</er>, <er>Culm</er>, <er>Shawm</er>,
<er>Calamus</er>.]</ety> <def>The denuded stems or stalks of such crops
as buckwheat and the cereal grains, beans, etc.; straw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haulm</ent>⟦br⟧

